      <!-- Winter2025 Term Project -->
      <div class="project-card">
        <img
          src="/images/AMS-project-screenshot.png"
          alt="Project preview"
          class="project-image"
        />

        <div class="project-content">
          <h2 class="project-title">Accomodation Management System</h2>
          <p class="project-description">
            A Python-based accommodation management system with a modern GUI
            built using CustomTkinter. It supports user authentication,
            reservations, suite management, and payment tracking, with JSON
            storage for persistent data. Designed for modularity and future
            scalability, the system demonstrates practical use of role-based
            access control and clean project structure.
          </p>

          <ul class="project-tags">
            <li>Python</li>
            <li>CustomTkinter</li>
            <li>GUI</li>
            <li>JSON Storage</li>
            <li>Role-Based Access Control</li>
            <li>OOP Principles</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="project-links" class="project-tags">
            <li>
              <a
                href="https://github.com/joshonline/hotel-management-system"
                target="_blank"
                >GitHub</a
              >
            </li>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Linux Backup Script -->
      <div class="project-card">
        <img
          src="/images/Fedora-backup-script.png"
          alt="Project preview"
          class="project-image"
        />

        <div class="project-content">
          <h2 class="project-title">Automated Linux Backup</h2>
          <p class="project-description">
            A set of custom Bash scripts for automating backups on both Ubuntu
            and Fedora systems. The scripts leverage rsync for efficient Home
            directory synchronization and integrate system-aware handling of
            different file system structures. This project strengthened my
            knowledge of Linux internals, file hierarchies, and shell scripting
            best practices. I continue to refine and expand these scripts for
            enhanced functionality and reliability.
          </p>

          <ul class="project-tags">
            <li>Linux</li>
            <li>Bash</li>
            <li>Shell Scripting</li>
            <li>Automation</li>
            <li>Rsync</li>
            <li>Ubuntu</li>
            <li>Fedora</li>
          </ul>

          <!-- <div class="project-links" class=""project-tags>
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/username/project" target="_blank">GitHub</a></li>
                    </div> -->
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Local Library WebApp - MDN Tutorial -->
      <div class="project-card">
        <!-- <img src="project-thumbnail.jpg" alt="Project preview" class="project-image" /> -->

        <div class="project-content">
          <h2 class="project-title">Local Library WebApp</h2>
          <p class="project-description">
            A Node.js + Express web application built as part of MDN's Learn Web
            Development course. The project manages a fictional library's book
            catalog with full CRUD functionality, using MongoDB for storage and
            Express routing for dynamic content. It served as a practical
            introduction to server-side rendering, RESTful APIs, and MVC
            architecture.
          </p>

          <ul class="project-tags">
            <li>Node.js</li>
            <li>Express.js</li>
            <li>npm basics</li>
            <li>MongoDB</li>
            <li>MVC</li>
            <li>RESTful APIs</li>
          </ul>

          <!-- <div class="project-links" class=""project-tags>
                    <li><a href="https://github.com/username/project" target="_blank">GitHub</a></li>
                </div> -->
